<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

  <head>
    <!--Meta Data-->
    <%- include('partial/title.ejs'); %> 

    <% if (data.NODE_ENV == 'production') { %>
      <!-- Production Stylesheets -->
      <link rel="stylesheet" href="assets/production/css/about.min.css">

    <% }else { %>
      <!-- Development Stylesheets -->
      <link rel="stylesheet" href="assets/lib/css/bootstrap.min.css">
      <link rel="stylesheet" href="assets/lib/css/fontawesome.min.css">
      <link rel="stylesheet" href="assets/lib/css/responsive.css">
      <link rel="stylesheet" href="assets/lib/css/select2.min.css">
      <link rel="stylesheet" href="assets/lib/css/spacing.css">
      <link rel="stylesheet" href="assets/lib/css/style.css">
      <link rel="stylesheet" href="assets/lib/css/owl.carousel.min.css">
      <link rel="stylesheet" href="assets/lib/css/bootstrap-datepicker.min.css">
      <link rel="stylesheet" href="assets/lib/css/magnific-popup.css">
      <link rel="stylesheet" href="assets/css/header.css">
      
    <% } %>
  </head>

  <body onLoad="typeWriter()">
    <!--Header-->
    <%- include('partial/header.ejs', {data: data }); %>

    <!--FAQ Start-->
    <div class="faq-area pt_60 pb_90">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-12">
            <div class="faq-group headstyle mt-30">
              <div id="accordion">
                <div class="faq-item card">
                  <div class="faq-header" id="heading1">
                    <button class="faq-button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapse1" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapse1"><i class="fa fa-caret-right"></i>Q: How secure is my patient data?</button>
                  </div>

                  <div id="collapse1" class="collapse show" aria-labelledby="heading1" data-parent="#accordion">
                    <div class="faq-body">
                      <p>A: We use bank‑level encryption (AES‑256) and comply with HIPAA and GDPR standards. Access is strictly role‑based, and every action is logged in an audit trail for complete transparency and accountability.</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item card">
                  <div class="faq-header" id="heading2">
                    <button class="faq-button collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapse2" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse2"><i class="fa fa-caret-right"></i>Q: Can patients book appointments online?</button>
                  </div>
                  <div id="collapse2" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="heading2" data-parent="#accordion">
                    <div class="faq-body">
                      <p>A: Yes. Through the patient portal or mobile app, patients can view doctor availability, schedule, reschedule, or cancel appointments in real time. Automated reminders are sent via email and SMS.</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item card">
                  <div class="faq-header" id="heading3">
                    <button class="faq-button collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapse3" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse3"><i class="fa fa-caret-right"></i>Q: How does the billing and insurance process work?</button>
                  </div>
                  <div id="collapse3" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="heading3" data-parent="#accordion">
                    <div class="faq-body">
                      <p>A: The system automatically generates invoices from consultations, procedures, pharmacy orders, and lab tests. It also supports insurance claims, co‑payments, and multiple payment methods (card, UPI, cash, etc.).</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item card">
                  <div class="faq-header" id="heading4">
                    <button class="faq-button collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapse4" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse4"><i class="fa fa-caret-right"></i>Q: Can I access my medical records electronically?</button>
                  </div>
                  <div id="collapse4" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="heading4" data-parent="#accordion">
                    <div class="faq-body">
                      <p>A: Absolutely. The Electronic Medical Records (EMR) module gives patients secure, anytime access to lab results, prescriptions, visit summaries, and imaging reports through their personal dashboard.</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item card">
                  <div class="faq-header" id="heading5">
                    <button class="faq-button collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapse5" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse5"><i class="fa fa-caret-right"></i>Q: How do I reset my password or get technical support?</button>
                  </div>
                  <div id="collapse5" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="heading5" data-parent="#accordion">
                    <div class="faq-body">
                      <p>A: Use the "Forgot Password" link on the login page. For technical support, our dedicated helpdesk is available 24/7 – email us at support@verohms.com or call our hotline.</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item card">
                  <div class="faq-header" id="heading6">
                    <button class="faq-button collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapse6" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse6"><i class="fa fa-caret-right"></i>Q: Is the system mobile‑friendly?</button>
                  </div>
                  <div id="collapse6" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="heading6" data-parent="#accordion">
                    <div class="faq-body">
                      <p>A: Yes. The web application is fully responsive for tablets and smartphones. We also offer dedicated mobile apps for iOS and Android, tailored for doctors, nurses, and patients.</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item card">
                  <div class="faq-header" id="heading7">
                    <button class="faq-button collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapse7" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse7"><i class="fa fa-caret-right"></i>Q: Can the system handle multiple hospital branches?</button>
                  </div>
                  <div id="collapse7" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="heading7" data-parent="#accordion">
                    <div class="faq-body">
                      <p>A: Yes. VERO HMS supports multi‑campus operations with centralized reporting, patient data sharing, and unified billing while maintaining separate branch‑level dashboards.</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item card">
                  <div class="faq-header" id="heading8">
                    <button class="faq-button collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapse8" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse8"><i class="fa fa-caret-right"></i>Q: How are laboratory and pharmacy orders integrated?</button>
                  </div>
                  <div id="collapse8" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="heading8" data-parent="#accordion">
                    <div class="faq-body">
                      <p>A: Orders placed by doctors appear instantly in the lab and pharmacy queues. Results and dispensation status are updated in real time and linked directly to the patient’s EMR for seamless care coordination.</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>

              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    </div>
    <!--FAQ End-->

    <!--Footer-->
    <%- include('partial/footer.ejs'); %>
    
    <script>
      var i = 0;
      var txt = 'WELCOME TO VERO HOSPITAL MANAGEMENT SYSTEM';
      var speed = 60;

      function typeWriter() {
        if (i < txt.length) {
          document.getElementById("typeit").innerHTML += txt.charAt(i);
          i++;
          setTimeout(typeWriter, speed);
        }
      }
    </script>

      <!-- JavaScript -->
    <script defer src="assets/lib/js/jquery-3.4.1.min.js"></script>
    <script defer src="assets/lib/js/popper.min.js"></script>
    <script defer src="assets/lib/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
    <script defer src="assets/lib/js/all.min.js"></script>
    <script defer src="assets/lib/js/select2.full.min.js"></script>
    <script defer src="assets/js/about.js"></script>
    
  </body>
</html>